{"word":"μεθύσκω","slug":"μεθύσκω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μεθύσκω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>Causal of <a href='S:μεθύω'><el>μεθύω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make drunk, intoxicate, inebriate</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to give to drink: to water, moisten</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> = <a href='S:μεθύω'><el>μεθύω</el></a>, <i>to drink freely, to get drunk</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; aor1 <el>ἐμεθύσθην</el>, <i>to be drunk</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>; <el>νέκταρος</el> <i>with</i> nectar, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}